what i said.<br>
<br>
i know why people poach Plane raids. i've acknowledged that the<br>
summitt isn't tuned to the timezone differences. <br>
<br>
you have however failed to acknowledge the fact that the primary<br>
reason for poaching anything is greed and overwhelming want for<br>
an epic, like Sandoval pointed out. poaching is *NOT* the only<br>
way for people in non-US timezones to get their epic, but it may<br>
be the easiest. <br>
<br>
what absolutely kills me is that when a plane has been poached by<br>
Guild A, and Guild B has it booked, then Guild B complains about it<br>
Guild A has the cheek so say &quot;oh it's only a game. don't take it<br>
so seriously.&quot; whole lot of hypocrisy. if Guild A didn't take it<br>
so seriously, why would they risk the ire of the rest of server<br>
and basically ignore community rules to poach planes. it's not<br>
consistent. poachers want others to chill out and take the poaching<br>
in a easier manner, but they themselves refuse to chill out and<br>
go ahead an poach regardless of consequences. <br>
<br>
btw, i agree with warrior epics being nonessential. warriors are <br>
tanks so HP and AC is most important, there are weapons that aren't<br>
epics but are pretty damn good too. no one is saying epics aren't<br>
good, but there is a difference between nice to have and being<br>
essential. as bard i'll tell you this, having a bard around may<br>
make things more convenient and nice because we enhance groups very<br>
well but i can't think of a situation where we are absolutely<br>
essential (maybe PoG pulling). then again i'm an old ultra-noobie,<br>
basically a walking oxymoron.  <br>
